---
title: Vegan One-Pan Corn & Bean Taco Salad with Pico de Gallo & Creamy Lime Dressing
description: This dinner idea is a study in culinary contrasts: a warm-cold, crunchy-creamy, earthy-herbal delight that will really make our Fresh Fam vegans smile. It starts with dressed salad greens and cilantro topped with warm, lightly charred corn (charring brings out the sweetness!) and black beans seasoned with savory Mexican-style spices. Top with bright pico de gallo, crumble crunchy tortilla chips over the bowl, and finish with a squeeze of lime juice for a tangy touch to this colorful 15-minute dinner salad.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/vegan-one-pan-corn-bean-taco-salad-9cefa850.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64762f872adaffbd433f8015.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: Mexican
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 3.5 g
  carbohydrates: 90 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 16 g
  fiber: 15 g
  sodium: 680 mg
course: main course
time required: 15 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-one-pan-corn-and-bean-taco-salad-64762f872adaffbd433f8015
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Drain @corn{1}, then pat dry with paper towels. Quarter @lime{1}.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; cut into bite-size pieces. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse @black beans{1}. Once corn is lightly charred, add drained beans, half the @fajita spice blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use more in the next step), and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} to pan; cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture is warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== Creamy Lime Dressing ==

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, whisk together @vegan mayo{2%tbsp}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, juice from half the lime (juice from whole lime for 4), a pinch of salt and pepper, and as much remaining fajita spice blend as you like.

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a dressing-like consistency (we used 2 tsp; 4 tsp for 4).

Add lettuce and cilantro to bowl with dressing and toss until thoroughly coated.

> This dinner idea is a study in culinary contrasts: a warm-cold, crunchy-creamy, earthy-herbal delight that will really make our Fresh Fam vegans smile.

> Charring brings out the sweetness in the corn!

== Assembly ==

Divide salad between #bowls{}; top with corn and bean mixture and @pico de gallo{4%ounce}. Crumble as many @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} as you like on top and serve with any remaining lime wedges.